<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 2:47PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Moore,
northeastern Montgomery, southern Randolph and southwestern Chatham
Counties through 330 PM EDT...
At 246 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Seagrove, or near North Carolina Zoo, moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Asheboro, Troy, North Carolina Zoo, Biscoe, Seagrove, Robbins, Star,
Steeds, Ulah and Harpers Crossroads.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
